<h2>Pagination</h2>
<p>The blocks-layer home for the <a href="/intents/collection-operations/">Collection Operations</a> intent's <strong><code>page</code> stage</strong>. It renders the paged controls the intent describes — numbered, prev/next, or load-more — inside a <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/landmark-regions/"><code>&lt;nav aria-label="pagination"&gt;</code></a> landmark with <code>aria-current="page"</code>, syncs the active page to a shareable self-canonical <code>?page=n</code> URL, and wires <code>advance:auto</code> to an <code>IntersectionObserver</code> scroll sentinel. Until this block existed the pagination standard described the <em>what</em> with no <em>how</em>; this is the runnable home for it.</p>

<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
  <strong>Terminology:</strong> See <a href="/semantics/">Semantics &amp; Glossary</a> for terms like
  <a href="/semantics/#term-aria-current">aria-current</a>,
  <a href="/semantics/#term-navigation-landmark">navigation landmark</a>,
  <a href="/semantics/#term-scroll-sentinel">scroll sentinel</a>,
  <a href="/semantics/#term-result-range-label">result-range label</a>, and
  <a href="/semantics/#term-deep-link">deep link</a>.
</p>

